reviewText:
What I think about SF V so far? Do you know that college assignment really hard that you have the entire term to do, but leave it to start just two days before the deadline? So, Capcom is looking like this student and SF V the assignment.

The game has a lot of unfinished parts and what is done looks unpolished.

Let's break it down:

The Good:

Gameplay feels good;
Graphics and physics looks really good;
V-system is a really nice addition to the game;
The art style is a little bit darker than SF IV, I would say somewhere between IV and Third Strike;
Crossplay
There is no El Fuerte.
The Bad:

Really poor character driven story mode, the majority of them feels silly;
Survival mode aka grind mode (the ideia to have a survival mode is nice, but here it is very bad implemented.);
No versus cpu mode;
No arcade mode;
Some scenarios are nice, but some of than are just a bunch of clichê, Compare Indian and Brazilian Stages from SF 2 to this SF and will get what I'm meaning. Back in a day they were much more original.
Some lazy animations - Look at Fang's super.
Matchmaking seems to be working for some people but for me is still getting around 15 minutes to find a match;
LAG!!!!! I need to wait about 15 minutes for the game to find a 5 Bar match to me and when it does, that is a big chance that the match will be unplayable due to lag (teleports + rollbacks);
A lot of different bugs - here is one that happened to me: http://steamcommunity.com/app/310950/discussions/0/405692758725659720/
Clipping models and textures:
[img] http://s27.postimg.org/eyfs3bzyb/2016_03_04_00012.jpg [/img]
[img] http://s27.postimg.org/7fs1gyj7n/2016_03_04_00004.jpg [/img]
[img] http://s27.postimg.org/v85y68amb/2016_03_04_00006.jpg [/img]

And that's it!

I'm still waiting to see about the plot from the main story mode... I hope they fix some of the continuity problems from the game, like Nash (Once back in a day, Nash was Blanka, Nash was killed in an explosion with Bison and now he was killed again by an helicopter...so far, so good....And also it would be nice if one day we could see the names from Bison, Vega, Balrog fixed)


I love the SF franchise and it is sad to me to make this review. Hope to see the game fixed soon, so I will be able to change my review.

Thanks for reading,

Bullfrog
